comments:
Abolished 1894 and divided into the parishes of Chalford and Bisley 
    with Lypiatt.

Created 1894 out of the separate parishes of Bisley and Lypiatt. 
    See also Table 2, note (s).

Created 26.3.1894 out of the parishes of Sonehouse and Stroud. 
    Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Stroud and King's Stanley.

Created 1.4.1990 out of the Stroud unparished area and the 
    parishes of Randwick and Stonehouse. See also Table 2, note (s).

Created 1894 out of the parish of Bisley. See also Table 2, note 
    (s).
Abolished 25.3.1884 and added to the parish of Stonehouse.

Created 1.4.1991 out of the parish of Hawkesbury. See also 
    Table 2, notes (r) and (s).
Created 1894 out of the parish of Stroud. Abolished 1894 and added to the parish of Bisley with Lypiatt.

Created 26.3.1892 out of the parishes of Horsley, Avening and 
    Minchinhampton. See also Table 2, note (s).

Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished area. See also Table 
    2, note (b).

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parish  of Stroud. 
    Abolished 1.4.1990 and divided between the parishes of Cainscross, 
    Rodborough and Stroud. See also Table 2, note (s).

Created 1.4.1990 out of the Stroud unparished area. See also 
    Table 2, note (s).

Created 1894 out of the parish of Stroud. See also Table 2, note 
    (s).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Painswick in Stroud 
    Urban District. Abolished 1.4.1936 and added to the parish of Stroud.

Created 1894 out of the parish of Stroud. Renamed 5.2.1987 to 
    become the parish of Whiteshill & Ruscombe.

Created 5.2.1987 by renaming the parish of Whiteshill. See also Table 2, note 
    (s).

That part which until 1.4.1935 formed part of the parish of Horsley. 
    See also Table 2, note (j).

That part which until 1.4.1935 formed part of the parish of 
    Stonehouse. See also Table 2, note (l).
